# Environment Configuration

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your values.

## Database

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://solarware:solarware_dev_password@localhost:5432/solarware
DATABASE_ECHO=false

## API Configuration

ENVIRONMENT=development
DEBUG=true
CORS_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173

## Satellite Providers (Optional)

# Google Earth Engine
GOOGLE_EARTH_ENGINE_PROJECT=your-project-id
GOOGLE_EARTH_ENGINE_KEY_FILE=./credentials/earth-engine-key.json

# Sentinel Hub
SENTINEL_HUB_CLIENT_ID=
SENTINEL_HUB_CLIENT_SECRET=

## Geocoding & Enrichment (Optional)

# Google Maps API
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=

# Google Custom Search
GOOGLE_SEARCH_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_SEARCH_ENGINE_ID=

## Solar Analysis Configuration

SOLAR_PANEL_WIDTH_M=1.75
SOLAR_PANEL_HEIGHT_M=1.05
SOLAR_PANEL_RATED_POWER_W=400
SYSTEM_EFFICIENCY=0.82
DEFAULT_COUNTRY=US

## Email Configuration (Optional)

# SMTP (Gmail, SendGrid, corporate, etc.)
SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USERNAME=
SMTP_PASSWORD=
SMTP_FROM_EMAIL=noreply@solarware.local
SMTP_FROM_NAME=Solarware

# SendGrid
SENDGRID_API_KEY=

# AWS SES
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
AWS_REGION=us-east-1

## Output Paths

OUTPUT_BASE_PATH=./output
MAILING_PACKS_PATH=./output/mailing_packs
VISUALIZATIONS_PATH=./output/visualizations

## Notes

1. DATABASE_URL format: postgresql://username:password@host:port/database
2. For development, use the docker-compose default or local PostgreSQL
3. API keys are optional - functionality degrades gracefully without them
4. Satellite providers both support free tiers
5. Email services: at least one should be configured for sending capability
